1
00:01:31,060 --> 00:01:35,030
[The Lost National Treasure]

2
00:01:35,070 --> 00:01:37,860
[Episode 33]

3
00:01:41,150 --> 00:01:42,810
Three Fingers has been found.

4
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,400
You've found him?

5
00:01:49,460 --> 00:01:52,530
[Baigou Village, Shangtong County]

6
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:53,240
Divorced?

7
00:01:54,430 --> 00:01:54,870
Yeah.

8
00:01:55,870 --> 00:01:56,509
When?

9
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:57,860
We got divorced

10
00:01:58,560 --> 00:02:00,160
the year my face got blown up.

11
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,350
Or what was I supposed to do?

12
00:02:02,350 --> 00:02:04,410
To wait for him to blow me up next time?

13
00:02:04,790 --> 00:02:06,120
What was he planning to blow up

14
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,180
using explosives?

15
00:02:07,510 --> 00:02:08,470
I don't know either.

16
00:02:08,470 --> 00:02:09,520
With his guts,

17
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,730
what could he possibly blow up?

18
00:02:13,590 --> 00:02:16,320
It was all because of the bad guy
who led him astray.

19
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,320
Who is the bad guy?

20
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,290
You know, the one

21
00:02:19,310 --> 00:02:20,470
with the long face

22
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,150
and curly hair

23
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:23,490
didn't talk much

24
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:25,570
and had a gloomy aura about him.

25
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:26,700
Oh, right.

26
00:02:26,910 --> 00:02:29,560
Liu Qiang even met with him
a few days before the incident.

27
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:30,430
Then when he came back,

28
00:02:30,430 --> 00:02:32,800
he was messing with fertilizer
in the house.

29
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,840
Who knew
he was actually making explosives?

30
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:36,000
If I had known,

31
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:37,750
I would have risked my life

32
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:39,150
to stop him from doing it.

33
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:42,290
Do you know what that man's name is?

34
00:02:42,470 --> 00:02:43,200
I don't know.

35
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:45,210
I had never seen him before.

36
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:48,930
Could you tell where he was
from by his accent?

37
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:50,240
From his accent,

38
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:52,440
he didn't sound like a local,

39
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:55,310
but he isn't from outside the province
either.

40
00:02:55,310 --> 00:02:56,640
He must be from Qinzhou.

41
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,590
Did Liu Qiang mention how he knew him?

42
00:03:00,590 --> 00:03:01,630
It must have been from before,

43
00:03:01,630 --> 00:03:03,870
when they were messing with explosives
at the mine, I guess.

44
00:03:03,870 --> 00:03:04,530
At the mine?

45
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:05,970
Which mine?

46
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:11,960
There's a place called Yongcheng
in the neighboring province.

47
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,590
On a mountain called Wulao Mountain,

48
00:03:13,590 --> 00:03:15,050
there's a phosphate mine.

49
00:03:15,190 --> 00:03:16,430
A lot of people from around here

50
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:18,490
used to work there blasting the mine.

51
00:03:19,710 --> 00:03:21,190
Has Liu Qiang contacted you recently?

52
00:03:21,190 --> 00:03:22,250
Not for a long time.

53
00:03:22,310 --> 00:03:24,240
He blew up my face like this,

54
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:26,240
and he's never given me a penny

55
00:03:26,710 --> 00:03:28,170
or even checked on me once.

56
00:03:32,030 --> 00:03:32,630
Oh, right.

57
00:03:32,750 --> 00:03:33,680
Why don't you ask

58
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,940
his father and mother?

59
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:37,150
Even if he wants to cut off contact,

60
00:03:37,150 --> 00:03:39,680
he still has to stay in touch
with his parents.

61
00:03:40,290 --> 00:03:41,490
We'll ask them later.

62
00:03:42,590 --> 00:03:42,920
Okay.

63
00:03:43,950 --> 00:03:44,950
Alright, I got it.

64
00:03:45,630 --> 00:03:47,150
Yongfu said he's checked it out.

65
00:03:47,150 --> 00:03:48,400
Those numbers
provided by Liu Qiang's parents

66
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:50,060
are temporary phone numbers.

67
00:03:50,710 --> 00:03:51,310
Forget it.

68
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,840
Even if we have the police station send
our men to keep an eye on it,

69
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:53,900
I doubt it'll work.

70
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:54,800
I think so too.

71
00:03:54,870 --> 00:03:55,870
Yongfu also said,

72
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:58,400
he only comes back
once every two or three years

73
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,080
and calls home once a month.

74
00:04:00,430 --> 00:04:02,030
Their house is in shambles.

75
00:04:02,030 --> 00:04:03,690
The roof is about to collapse.

76
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:06,560
People like him
have a nouveau riche mentality.

77
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:07,150
When they make some money,

78
00:04:07,150 --> 00:04:09,030
they can't wait to blow it all.

79
00:04:09,190 --> 00:04:11,320
They just leave their parents behind.

80
00:04:11,470 --> 00:04:12,190
So where are we going now?

81
00:04:12,190 --> 00:04:13,240
Wulao Mountain, Yongcheng.

82
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:14,680
Let's go to the mine and ask around.

83
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:15,960
The person Liu Qiang's ex-wife mentioned

84
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:18,240
should be the one who recruited Liu Qiang.

85
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:19,890
We might be able
to dig up something from him.

86
00:04:19,890 --> 00:04:20,269
Okay.

87
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:24,160
What's wrong?

88
00:04:24,290 --> 00:04:24,730
Qiang,

89
00:04:25,070 --> 00:04:25,800
I heard from Lin

90
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,310
that two men went to Baigou Village today.

91
00:04:27,310 --> 00:04:28,680
They were looking for your wife.

92
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:29,770
Seems like they're cops.

93
00:04:29,770 --> 00:04:30,970
Don't show yourself.

94
00:04:48,270 --> 00:04:50,240
Stingy Wu, what's wrong with you?

95
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:51,720
Don't you know
the cases have been consolidated?

96
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:54,940
Report any situation to me,
your leader, promptly.

97
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:55,990
Cut the crap.

98
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:59,159
Can't you say something nice
when you call me?

99
00:04:59,159 --> 00:05:00,560
These past two days, Liu Gang and I

100
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:02,360
have delved into caves non-stop.

101
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,560
We took turns driving

102
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:04,480
and sleeping.

103
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:06,360
We've been both exhausted.

104
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:07,720
You don't even
show a bit of consideration.

105
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:09,000
And here you are, demanding explanations.

106
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,380
What kind of leader are you?

107
00:05:10,380 --> 00:05:11,870
I'm asking you to report,

108
00:05:11,870 --> 00:05:13,000
not to complain.

109
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:14,260
Tell me,

110
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:16,040
how's the investigation
on that person going?

111
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,740
The phosphate mine
has long been closed down.

112
00:05:17,740 --> 00:05:19,400
We've asked around quite a bit

113
00:05:19,430 --> 00:05:22,520
and finally found out about
Liu Qiang's former foreman.

114
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:24,320
He might know about that person.

115
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,090
What do you mean by "might"?

116
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:27,640
Are you an inexperienced schoolboy?

117
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:29,360
Give me definite information.

118
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,650
The man has already retired.

119
00:05:30,650 --> 00:05:31,800
He lives in Qinchuan.

120
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:33,200
We're on our way back now.

121
00:05:35,270 --> 00:05:36,120
Mr. Zhu!

122
00:05:38,610 --> 00:05:40,210
We have something to ask you.

123
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:42,200
What is it?

124
00:05:42,430 --> 00:05:43,560
Come on, have a seat.

125
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:47,600
You look in great shape.

126
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:50,560
Thanks to doing exercise.

127
00:05:54,140 --> 00:05:55,830
I'm from the Public Security Bureau.

128
00:05:55,830 --> 00:05:57,760
I'd like to inquire about someone.

129
00:05:58,360 --> 00:05:59,690
Inquire about someone?

130
00:05:59,950 --> 00:06:00,560
Who?

131
00:06:00,750 --> 00:06:01,600
Ten years ago,

132
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,310
did you work at the phosphate mine
on Wulao Mountain

133
00:06:03,310 --> 00:06:04,040
as a foreman?

134
00:06:04,190 --> 00:06:06,250
I was from the technical department.

135
00:06:06,310 --> 00:06:08,310
Do you know someone named Liu Qiang?

136
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:09,950
Liu Qiang?

137
00:06:12,510 --> 00:06:13,830
You mean Qiang?

138
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,640
He's also from Qinchuan.

139
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,410
We're from the same hometown.

140
00:06:17,630 --> 00:06:18,560
Did he have someone

141
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:20,220
quite close to him at the mine?

142
00:06:21,430 --> 00:06:23,560
I don't know about that.

143
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,410
Anyway, this kid

144
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:26,870
couldn't handle the hard work.

145
00:06:26,870 --> 00:06:29,070
He didn't stay for long before leaving.

146
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,320
Think about it again.

147
00:06:35,950 --> 00:06:37,870
Was he close to someone

148
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,570
from the blasting team?

149
00:06:40,830 --> 00:06:42,000
The blasting team?

150
00:06:45,020 --> 00:06:45,880
I remember now.

151
00:06:46,830 --> 00:06:47,830
During that time,

152
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:51,040
everyone at the mine was talking about it.

153
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:52,600
They said Qiang

154
00:06:53,270 --> 00:06:56,000
went back to mix explosives
and blew up his house.

155
00:06:56,630 --> 00:06:58,890
He even did a few years in prison
for that.

156
00:06:59,390 --> 00:07:00,310
They said back then,

157
00:07:00,310 --> 00:07:02,310
he was called away by a blaster.

158
00:07:02,870 --> 00:07:04,470
What's this blaster's name?

159
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:08,000
I don't know his name. All I know is that

160
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:09,110
he was a loner,

161
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,730
who didn't talk much

162
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,050
and avoided crowds.

163
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,560
But you see, this young man

164
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,270
was quite skilled at blasting.

165
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:18,000
What did this person look like?

166
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,680
What did he look like?

167
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:22,560
He had a long face.

168
00:07:23,430 --> 00:07:24,560
He was tall and thin,

169
00:07:25,390 --> 00:07:26,320
with curly hair.

170
00:07:27,250 --> 00:07:29,250
He was about 20 years old at the time.

171
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,130
What accent did he have?

172
00:07:32,030 --> 00:07:34,150
It seemed to be a Qinchuan accent.

173
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,630
So, this Liu Qiang

174
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:39,480
is not a blaster.

175
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:42,409
He's just an ordinary
construction technician.

176
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:46,870
The person his ex-wife told Zhu Guoqing

177
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,240
is a blaster.

178
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,560
He should be

179
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:54,650
Gunner we're looking for.

180
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:56,920
I just interrogated Liang again.

181
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:57,800
He also said

182
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,950
that this Gunner is a tall, thin guy,

183
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:02,090
who looks to be in his thirties.

184
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,560
If we go back about 10 years,

185
00:08:05,070 --> 00:08:08,240
he should be in his twenties,
just as Zhu Guoqing mentioned.

186
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:10,160
I also agree with what Chief Wu said.

187
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:10,560
Look,

188
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:11,820
what Liang,

189
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:13,120
Liu Qiang's ex-wife,

190
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:15,160
and Zhu Guoqing said

191
00:08:15,510 --> 00:08:16,910
has something in common.

192
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:17,400
Quiet,

193
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:18,760
ruthless,

194
00:08:19,270 --> 00:08:20,070
tall and thin,

195
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:21,170
with curly hair,

196
00:08:21,270 --> 00:08:22,000
right age,

197
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,310
and most importantly,

198
00:08:23,310 --> 00:08:25,310
blasting experience.

199
00:08:26,830 --> 00:08:27,360
Alright.

200
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,160
Since we all agree,

201
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,450
we'll split into two teams.

202
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:35,320
One team will search for Liu Qiang,

203
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:38,480
and the other will dig for information
on Gunner.

204
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:39,750
However, we know very little

205
00:08:39,750 --> 00:08:41,510
about Gunner.

206
00:08:42,510 --> 00:08:44,270
If there's really no other way,

207
00:08:45,030 --> 00:08:47,030
we'll have to use the hard way again.

208
00:08:47,030 --> 00:08:48,240
Be prepared.

209
00:08:49,150 --> 00:08:49,960
Qi Dacang,

210
00:08:50,970 --> 00:08:52,630
you're hinting at something.

211
00:08:52,690 --> 00:08:54,300
What do you mean by "the hard way"?

212
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:56,890
I have my own way
of doing things the hard way.

213
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:59,210
I'll keep digging for clues about Gunner.

214
00:08:59,210 --> 00:09:00,120
I don't believe

215
00:09:00,150 --> 00:09:01,550
we can't get the information we want

216
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:02,600
after we question all the old workers
from his time at the mine,

217
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:04,150
one by one.

218
00:09:04,550 --> 00:09:05,960
Listen to him. What an admirable spirit!

219
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,090
Learn from Chief Wu!

220
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:07,750
Good!

221
00:09:08,110 --> 00:09:08,440
Good!

222
00:09:08,510 --> 00:09:09,200
Alright.

223
00:09:09,870 --> 00:09:10,500
Everyone, stop.

224
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:16,790
[Kangning Hospital, Qingyuan County]

225
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,000
Nurse.

226
00:09:46,910 --> 00:09:47,340
Where's the patient?

227
00:09:47,340 --> 00:09:49,340
Left, just discharged not long ago.

228
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:50,360
Discharged?

229
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:04,760
Hey, Jianhui.

230
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:05,240
Guang,

231
00:10:05,630 --> 00:10:06,430
where are you?

232
00:10:07,030 --> 00:10:08,840
Why are you running around
at a time like this?

233
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:09,300
I'm not.

234
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,320
I'm on my way

235
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:13,750
to the old town in Jiaocheng
to find Wen Wen.

236
00:10:13,750 --> 00:10:15,080
Wen Wen is in Jiaocheng?

237
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:16,860
Wait for me.

238
00:10:17,010 --> 00:10:18,270
I'm coming right away.

239
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:28,050
[Jiaocheng]

240
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:41,570
Excuse me, may I ask something?

241
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,520
Have you seen this woman?

242
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,000
Haven't seen her.

243
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:51,250
What do you want?

244
00:10:51,790 --> 00:10:53,360
Have you seen this woman?

245
00:10:58,440 --> 00:10:59,570
She looks familiar.

246
00:10:59,910 --> 00:11:00,440
Yan,

247
00:11:00,750 --> 00:11:02,010
come here for a second.

248
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:06,360
Is she the one selling yogurt
at the corner over there?

249
00:11:07,630 --> 00:11:08,510
Looks like it.

250
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:09,940
Which corner?

251
00:11:10,150 --> 00:11:12,280
The one selling yogurt at that corner.

252
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:13,350
Thank you.

253
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:34,670
Guang.

254
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:37,390
Guang.

255
00:11:38,250 --> 00:11:38,780
Jianhui.

256
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:40,100
How are you?

257
00:11:40,790 --> 00:11:41,440
I'm fine.

258
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:42,880
Let's go.

259
00:11:42,880 --> 00:11:43,740
Don't touch me.

260
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:46,910
Just don't touch me now.

261
00:11:47,690 --> 00:11:49,490
Let's find a hotel to stay first.

262
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:57,250
Someone just told me

263
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:00,630
Wen Wen is in that yogurt shop ahead.

264
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:02,790
I want to go see her.

265
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,680
You want to see her like this?

266
00:12:07,290 --> 00:12:08,690
I just want to take a look.

267
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:14,880
Listen to me.

268
00:12:15,790 --> 00:12:17,240
Let's find a hotel to stay first.

269
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:18,910
I'll go look for her for you later.

270
00:12:18,910 --> 00:12:19,550
No.

271
00:12:21,910 --> 00:12:23,080
I need to find out

272
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:27,240
why she left me and the kid.

273
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,610
She's already left.

274
00:12:32,470 --> 00:12:33,960
Is there any point in asking now?

275
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:34,490
There is.

276
00:12:37,630 --> 00:12:39,760
I don't have many loved ones in my life.

277
00:12:42,050 --> 00:12:43,110
You're one of them.

278
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:45,630
So is Wen Wen.

279
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:48,560
If I don't get the answer,

280
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:52,490
I'll never have peace of mind
in this life.

281
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:07,970
You really want to know the answer
that badly?

282
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:14,920
