00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:12,720
Dad,

566
00:32:13,310 --> 00:32:14,680
phones don't use buttons anymore.

567
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:16,030
They all use touchscreens now.

568
00:32:16,030 --> 00:32:16,890
Touchscreens?

569
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:18,540
How do I make calls?

570
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:19,960
Come here, kid.

571
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:21,840
Install some applications for your dad.

572
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:22,270
Okay.

573
00:32:23,110 --> 00:32:24,240
This is a phone book.

574
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:26,040
You can make a call by tapping it.

575
00:32:26,940 --> 00:32:27,940
Then you tap this.

576
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:29,210
Scroll down.

577
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:31,000
Camera.

578
00:32:31,310 --> 00:32:32,640
It's for taking photos.

579
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:34,690
It can even take pictures.

580
00:32:34,690 --> 00:32:35,400
Let's take one.

581
00:32:35,400 --> 00:32:36,530
Come on. Let's do it.

582
00:32:38,070 --> 00:32:38,930
Mom, look here.

583
00:32:45,110 --> 00:32:46,370
-Let me see.
-Who is it?

584
00:32:47,750 --> 00:32:48,280
Who is it?

585
00:32:48,750 --> 00:32:49,750
Look at yourself.

586
00:32:50,590 --> 00:32:51,250
Yan Xiaowu.

587
00:32:52,720 --> 00:32:54,870
There's something we need you
to come to the station for

588
00:32:54,870 --> 00:32:57,000
to cooperate with the investigation.

589
00:32:59,750 --> 00:33:01,010
What's the matter now?

590
00:33:01,180 --> 00:33:03,110
We'll talk about it at the station.

591
00:33:10,030 --> 00:33:10,830
It's nothing.

592
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:11,930
Don't worry.

593
00:33:12,350 --> 00:33:13,350
I'll be back soon.

594
00:33:14,830 --> 00:33:15,430
Take this.

595
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:17,200
Bao.

596
00:33:17,790 --> 00:33:19,250
Have dinner with your mom.

597
00:33:20,590 --> 00:33:21,120
Let's go.

598
00:33:23,510 --> 00:33:23,880
Dad.

599
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:44,200
Mr. Mu.

600
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:45,580
Captain Qi.

601
00:33:47,070 --> 00:33:48,070
Here on business?

602
00:33:48,790 --> 00:33:50,030
Are you heading out?

603
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:55,360
Well, it's like this.

604
00:33:55,750 --> 00:33:57,790
We've encountered a tricky case.

605
00:33:58,310 --> 00:34:00,590
We need the help of an expert like you.

606
00:34:02,680 --> 00:34:03,680
What kind of case?

607
00:34:04,900 --> 00:34:07,760
Let's discuss it in detail at the station,
shall we?

608
00:34:08,699 --> 00:34:09,880
What's the nature of it?

609
00:34:09,880 --> 00:34:10,810
Tell me clearly.

610
00:34:11,070 --> 00:34:12,400
So my wife won't worry.

611
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:13,960
Take a look at this,

612
00:34:14,670 --> 00:34:16,000
and you'll understand.

613
00:34:20,110 --> 00:34:20,880
A summons?

614
00:34:21,630 --> 00:34:24,070
The detention time for a summons
won't exceed 24 hours.

615
00:34:24,070 --> 00:34:25,270
Shulan, don't worry.

616
00:34:25,320 --> 00:34:26,400
I'll be back soon.

617
00:34:27,630 --> 00:34:28,400
We have a car.

618
00:34:28,750 --> 00:34:29,280
Alright.

619
00:34:29,389 --> 00:34:29,850
Please.

620
00:34:30,260 --> 00:34:30,850
Let's go.

621
00:34:34,580 --> 00:34:36,110
I bought that book of yours.

622
00:34:36,150 --> 00:34:37,280
It's well-written.

623
00:34:37,630 --> 00:34:38,760
How can I let you pay?

624
00:34:39,150 --> 00:34:41,350
-Of course.
-I can give you one for free.

625
00:34:41,670 --> 00:34:44,070
I'll reimburse you for whatever you spent.

626
00:35:15,030 --> 00:35:15,590
Xiaowu.

627
00:35:16,820 --> 00:35:17,950
When did you get out?

628
00:35:18,870 --> 00:35:20,400
You didn't even contact me.

629
00:35:20,840 --> 00:35:21,570
Just got out.

630
00:35:26,920 --> 00:35:28,520
Haven't seen you in 10 years.

631
00:35:28,630 --> 00:35:29,760
I really missed you.

632
00:35:32,850 --> 00:35:34,310
You've got white hair too.

633
00:35:35,590 --> 00:35:36,790
We've both grown old.

634
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:39,050
Old acquaintances.

635
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:42,360
Then we have a lot to talk about.

636
00:35:43,480 --> 00:35:44,410
Let's go inside.

637
00:35:45,070 --> 00:35:45,870
Take our time.

638
00:35:46,440 --> 00:35:47,300
We'll catch up.

639
00:35:50,070 --> 00:35:51,000
I'll go in first.

640
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:56,450
Let's go.

641
00:36:04,260 --> 00:36:05,350
I didn't expect

642
00:36:05,990 --> 00:36:08,780
that you were so close to Yan Xiaowu.

643
00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:11,940
Captain Qi,

644
00:36:12,770 --> 00:36:14,100
do you have any friends?

645
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:15,640
Of course I do,

646
00:36:16,320 --> 00:36:17,050
but not many.

647
00:36:17,840 --> 00:36:18,700
We're the same.

648
00:36:20,030 --> 00:36:21,190
Making friends needs real honesty.

649
00:36:21,190 --> 00:36:23,000
Watering a tree should
start from its roots.

650
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:24,510
Whether someone is a true friend

651
00:36:24,510 --> 00:36:26,770
can only be seen when you're down and out.

652
00:36:27,230 --> 00:36:28,290
Come to think of it,

653
00:36:28,710 --> 00:36:30,320
for most of my life,

654
00:36:30,880 --> 00:36:32,150
I was down on my luck.

655
00:36:33,150 --> 00:36:34,280
But I've been fortunate enough

656
00:36:34,280 --> 00:36:35,940
to marry a kind-hearted woman

657
00:36:36,070 --> 00:36:37,600
and make a few true buddies.

658
00:36:38,300 --> 00:36:40,030
Yan Xiaowu is one of them.

659
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:42,480
I remember

660
00:36:42,730 --> 00:36:44,590
when I asked you in prison before,

661
00:36:44,590 --> 00:36:47,510
you said you didn't have much to do
with Mu Jianhui.

662
00:36:48,280 --> 00:36:49,550
But just now outside,

663
00:36:49,710 --> 00:36:52,230
you two didn't look like strangers.

664
00:36:54,670 --> 00:36:56,480
Anyone can say nice things.

665
00:36:58,230 --> 00:36:59,830
If we were really that close,

666
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:01,970
I was in prison for 10 years,

667
00:37:02,260 --> 00:37:04,060
yet he didn't even come to see me.

668
00:37:08,110 --> 00:37:10,370
It's not that he didn't want to visit you.

669
00:37:11,030 --> 00:37:13,360
He was deliberately avoiding suspicion.

670
00:37:15,670 --> 00:37:16,330
Yan Xiaowu,

671
00:37:17,390 --> 00:37:18,790
let me tell you the truth.

672
00:37:20,440 --> 00:37:22,300
We've understood the situation.

673
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:25,320
Wang Jiahao,

674
00:37:27,730 --> 00:37:29,550
the one you call King Hua,

675
00:37:31,670 --> 00:37:33,200
has confessed everything.

676
00:37:34,630 --> 00:37:35,230
Back then,

677
00:37:36,320 --> 00:37:37,440
the person who sold

678
00:37:38,320 --> 00:37:39,930
the black pottery figurine to him

679
00:37:39,930 --> 00:37:41,480
wasn't you at all.

680
00:37:46,260 --> 00:37:47,260
It was Mu Jianhui.

681
00:37:47,900 --> 00:37:48,480
Right?

682
00:37:57,220 --> 00:37:58,840
You see, this Mu Jianhui

683
00:38:00,510 --> 00:38:02,440
didn't hide his friendship with you

684
00:38:02,440 --> 00:38:04,190
at all, did he?

685
00:38:11,630 --> 00:38:12,670
Mu Jianhui

686
00:38:14,510 --> 00:38:15,030
indeed

687
00:38:16,310 --> 00:38:17,610
helped me a lot.

688
00:38:18,710 --> 00:38:19,800
I heard that

689
00:38:21,190 --> 00:38:22,650
when Yan Xiaowu was young,

690
00:38:23,550 --> 00:38:24,550
he

691
00:38:24,970 --> 00:38:26,460
stole his mother's dowry

692
00:38:27,190 --> 00:38:28,590
to spend on his buddy.

693
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:32,400
That buddy wouldn't happen to be you,
would it?

694
00:38:33,630 --> 00:38:35,890
This kind of plot only happens in movies.

695
00:38:36,400 --> 00:38:38,330
How could it possibly happen to me?

696
00:38:39,590 --> 00:38:41,660
Xiaowu was competitive when he was young.

697
00:38:41,660 --> 00:38:43,150
He was the ringleader of the kids.

698
00:38:43,150 --> 00:38:45,920
What he did was just his way
of trying to be the ringleader

699
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:46,440
by winning over

700
00:38:46,440 --> 00:38:48,170
those little kids, that's all.

701
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:51,160
Didn't you guys find out?

702
00:38:51,670 --> 00:38:54,800
He was actually the one
who bullied me the most back then.

703
00:38:54,920 --> 00:38:55,280
What?

704
00:38:56,400 --> 00:38:57,130
Bullied you?

705
00:38:58,710 --> 00:39:00,840
Back then, except for Shulan,

706
00:39:01,510 --> 00:39:03,440
who in the factory didn't bully me?

707
00:39:06,030 --> 00:39:06,880
That's weird.

708
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:09,290
Then how did you two become friends again?

709
00:39:11,190 --> 00:39:12,230
It's a long story.

710
00:39:13,630 --> 00:39:16,760
That year, Yan Xiaowu's mother
got heart disease.

711
00:39:17,190 --> 00:39:18,920
To raise money for the surgery,

712
00:39:19,150 --> 00:39:21,550
he begged everyone in the factory.

713
00:39:21,670 --> 00:39:23,470
He almost kowtowed to everyone.

714
00:39:23,550 --> 00:39:24,760
Those who used to be

715
00:39:24,920 --> 00:39:26,400
so close to him,

716
00:39:26,880 --> 00:39:28,590
treated him as their big brother,

717
00:39:28,590 --> 00:39:30,360
and ate and drank with him every day,

718
00:39:30,360 --> 00:39:33,020
as close as if they shared
the same pair of pants,

719
00:39:33,480 --> 00:39:35,150
all disappeared overnight.

720
00:39:38,400 --> 00:39:39,150
That day,

721
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:43,590
I bought my mom her favorite egg cake.

722
00:39:48,230 --> 00:39:49,000
After that,

723
00:39:50,880 --> 00:39:52,840
I went to the bathroom

724
00:39:53,670 --> 00:39:54,930
and cried my heart out.

725
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:58,000
I was about to take her home

726
00:39:58,550 --> 00:39:59,750
to wait for her death.

727
00:40:01,510 --> 00:40:02,360
Who knew

728
00:40:03,760 --> 00:40:06,030
a nurse came to tell me

729
00:40:07,140 --> 00:40:10,230
someone had paid the surgery fee for me.

730
00:40:12,670 --> 00:40:15,070
It couldn't have been Mu Jianhui,
could it?

731
00:40:17,150 --> 00:40:19,670
He brought me

732
00:40:21,190 --> 00:40:22,190
all his money.

733
00:40:26,230 --> 00:40:27,110
The surgery fee

734
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:28,930
was just enough.

735
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:32,430
Well,

736
00:40:33,590 --> 00:40:36,280
why would you give everything

737
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:38,800
to help someone

738
00:40:39,360 --> 00:40:40,880
who bullied you the most?

739
00:40:44,020 --> 00:40:47,690
Maybe I'm just good
at putting myself in others' shoes.

740
00:40:49,230 --> 00:40:51,110
Even though my own life wasn't great,

741
00:40:51,110 --> 00:40:53,530
I still couldn't bear
to see others suffer.

742
00:40:55,320 --> 00:40:57,280
Anyway, I was all alone,

743
00:40:57,710 --> 00:40:59,510
and I didn't have many expenses.

744
00:40:59,710 --> 00:41:01,840
Money was the least useful thing to me.

745
00:41:06,320 --> 00:41:06,780
Well...

746
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:10,320
You're so virtuous.

747
00:41:12,070 --> 00:41:14,440
Were you born

748
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:16,030
to be kind

749
00:41:16,670 --> 00:41:17,710
and compassionate,

750
00:41:17,710 --> 00:41:20,280
or did you learn

751
00:41:20,510 --> 00:41:22,400
from Confucianism, Buddhism, Taoism,

752
00:41:22,400 --> 00:41:23,950
or something like them later?

753
00:41:23,950 --> 00:41:25,080
I don't know either.

754
00:41:25,760 --> 00:41:27,040
This is really rare.

755
00:41:31,670 --> 00:41:32,510
But

756
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:34,800
why do I feel

757
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:37,380
there might be other possibilities?

758
00:41:38,190 --> 00:41:39,450
Tell me what you think.

759
00:41:40,550 --> 00:41:41,280
For example,

760
00:41:42,880 --> 00:41:43,760
you think

761
00:41:44,760 --> 00:41:46,220
controlling human nature

762
00:41:47,160 --> 00:41:47,930
is fun.

763
00:41:49,800 --> 00:41:50,230
Do you?

764
00:41:54,540 --> 00:41:55,200
Captain Qi,

765
00:41:56,170 --> 00:41:57,570
why do you think that way?

766
00:41:59,310 --> 00:42:00,180
Well,

767
00:42:01,590 --> 00:42:02,720
it's just a feeling.

768
00:42:03,710 --> 00:42:05,440
Because I can't understand it.

769
00:42:05,590 --> 00:42:06,920
Not holding a grudge

770
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:08,960
is already great.

771
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:13,640
But you repaid evil with kindness
and gave away everything you had.

772
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:14,640
I think

773
00:42:15,480 --> 00:42:16,630
it must be that you

774
00:42:18,840 --> 00:42:20,170
understand Yan Xiaowu,

775
00:42:21,670 --> 00:42:22,320
so you can

776
00:42:22,960 --> 00:42:24,070
control his mind.

777
00:42:25,320 --> 00:42:26,650
I don't know what method

778
00:42:27,760 --> 00:42:28,480
you used.

779
00:42:29,230 --> 00:42:30,030
But anyway,

780
00:42:30,760 --> 00:42:32,360
you made him willingly

781
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:33,880
take the blame

782
00:42:34,710 --> 00:42:36,030
and go to jail for you.

783
00:42:36,750 --> 00:42:37,350
Am I right?

784
00:42:37,590 --> 00:42:38,650
Are you kidding me?

785
00:42:39,880 --> 00:42:41,480
How would I know

786
00:42:41,590 --> 00:42:43,250
what law Yan Xiaowu violated?

787
00:42:44,590 --> 00:42:45,920
King Hua has confessed.

788
00:42:48,030 --> 00:42:48,800
King Hua?

789
00:42:49,110 --> 00:42:49,920
What King Hua?

790
00:42:51,460 --> 00:42:53,180
King Hua has been arrested.

791
00:42:54,110 --> 00:42:55,710
He's confessed everything.

792
00:42:55,800 --> 00:42:56,710
Ten years ago,

793
00:42:57,630 --> 00:43:01,030
the one who sold him the black
pottery figurine wasn't Yan Xiaowu

794
00:43:01,030 --> 00:43:01,550
but you.
